.TH LINUX-HELLO-PAM-CONFIRM 1 "December 2025" "linux-hello 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
linux-hello-pam-confirm \- GUI confirmation dialog for Linux Hello PAM authentication

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B linux-hello-pam-confirm
.BI --username= USERNAME
.BI --pipe= FIFO_PATH
[\fB--no-gui\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Displays a graphical confirmation dialog after successful facial recognition.
This script is automatically launched by the PAM module and supports multiple desktop environments.

.SS Desktop Environment Support
.IP KDE
Uses \fBkdialog\fR for native KDE dialogs if available (recommended)
.IP GNOME/XFCE
Falls back to \fBzenity\fR if kdialog unavailable
.IP Generic
Uses PySide6 GUI as final fallback

.SS Desktop Notifications
Sends D-Bus notifications at each stage:
.IP "Recognition in progress"
When facial recognition starts
.IP "Confirmation received"
When user clicks Confirm/Cancel button

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --username= USERNAME
Username to display in the confirmation dialog (required)
.TP
.BI --pipe= FIFO_PATH
Path to FIFO pipe for response communication (required)
.TP
.B --no-gui
Headless mode \(en disable GUI, use CLI only (optional)

.SH EXIT STATUS
.IP 0
Dialog was properly handled and response written to FIFO
.IP 1
Error writing response or missing arguments
.IP >1
GUI framework error (PySide6, D-Bus, etc.)

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Display confirmation for user 'john':
.B linux-hello-pam-confirm --username=john --pipe=/run/linux-hello-pam/john.fifo

.TP
Test with dialog visible in current session:
.B DISPLAY=:0 linux-hello-pam-confirm --username=$USER --pipe=/tmp/test.fifo

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DISPLAY
X11 display for GUI output (e.g., \fI:0\fR, \fI:1\fR)
.TP
.B XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP
Detected desktop environment (KDE, GNOME, XFCE, etc.)
.TP
.B HOME
User home directory

.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/lib/linux-hello/linux-hello-pam-confirm.py
Python helper script
.TP
.I /run/linux-hello-pam/
Runtime directory for FIFO pipes

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pam_linux_hello (8),
.BR kdialog (1),
.BR zenity (1),
.BR systemd-run (1)

.SH AUTHOR
Linux Hello Project
